<title>FRANCE: Giscard d'Estaing hopes Italy in first EMU wave.</title>
<headline>Giscard d'Estaing hopes Italy in first EMU wave.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-03-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Former French president Valery Giscard d'Estaing said on Friday it was &quot;very desirable&quot; that Italy should be part of the first wave of countries to join Europe's planned single currency.</p>
<p>Speaking on French radio during a visit to Rome, Giscard hailed the Italian government's efforts to overhaul its budget in time to meet the criteria for joining European Monetary Union in 1999.</p>
<p>Italy's austerity measures involved &quot;very large and courageous amounts in order to be able meet the rendezvous for a single currency&quot;, he said.</p>
<p>&quot;We must salute these considerable efforts and wish them success,&quot; Giscard told RTL national radio.</p>
</text>
